text: The Australian Electoral Commission (AEC) has urged the Federal Court to dismiss cases against Treasurer Josh Frydenberg and Liberal MP Gladys Liu after they were each accused of using official AEC branding in mandarin election signs. Complainants argued signs deliberately misled voters by replicating official AEC branding. The case against Mr Frydenberg was filed by his unsuccessful Independent challenger Oliver Yates who is seeking to force a by-election in Kooyong. The AEC argued it was impossible to know whether voters changed their ballot based on the signs. Image: News Corp Australia
